 841:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4F/port.c ****         /* Priority grouping:  The interrupt controller (NVIC) allows the bits
 842:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4F/port.c ****          * that define each interrupt's priority to be split between bits that
 843:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4F/port.c ****          * define the interrupt's pre-emption priority bits and bits that define
 844:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4F/port.c ****          * the interrupt's sub-priority.  For simplicity all bits must be defined
 845:Middlewares/Third_Party/FreeRTOS/Source/portable/GCC/ARM_CM4F/port.c ****          * to be pre-emption priority bits.  The following assertion will fail if
